==Finnish==
===Etymology===
A borrowing of Common Germanic *''[[lambaz]]''. As Finnish seems to be a very conservative language (i.e., it usually retains the basic structure of the language it had borrowed from), the Finnish word shows how a masculine noun looked like in the Common Germanic language.
===Noun===
'''lammas'''

# [[sheep]]

